				h1 Off-The-Record

			section
				h2.bullet Off-The-Record basics
				h3.bullet IM + privacy = Off-The-Record
				h3.bullet OTR encrypts your chat messages so that no one read your conversations.
				h3.bullet Not even the chat service.

			section
				h2.bullet The tech
				h3.bullet OTR manages your keys for you.
				h3.bullet You just turn it on, challenge the other person with a question that only they would know (to make sure that it's really them), and talk
				h3.bullet One caveat: OTR only works after the first message. (Consult your threat model.)

			section
				h2.bullet So how do I use it?
				h3.bullet Get <a href="https://pidgin.im">Pidgin</a> or <a href="https://adium.im/">Adium</a> (for Macs) and turn on the OTR plugin.
				h3.bullet Start a chat and click on the OTR icon. Follow the prompts.
				h3.bullet Congrats! Your conversation is now encrypted.

			section
				h2.bullet Obligatory warning
				h3.bullet If you are a highly-targeted individual, or are especially paranoid, do not use Pidgin.
				h3.bullet Your risks are different and you must act accordingly.
				h3.bullet Talk to me afterwards and I can explain why.

